reviews.review_text:
Toughest ever 4 me This was the toughest show ever for me to get a ticket for, at one point my girlfriend and I turned to leave for the hotel. ( Apple Inn ) Anyone remember that Apple inn?  We had 1 ticket between us she the organized one with a real job had scored a mail order ticket . Me being a strung out junkie at this point did not have much going for me at this point in life. Debated on selling her ticket we made our mind up that we were going to find someone we knew and give it them.... Just as we were getting ready to give it away Dread John came around the corner and told me had me a back stage pass and had been looking for me for awhile. Off we went and in we go just like every other night smiling and happy could now settle into the show. I for the very 1st and only time went way up back as far from stage as we could get and laid out a few app's when they kicked it off we did too. Being most of our favorite place we went our own ways till the new years count down. 
 Sorry not about the sound more the story of how lucky we were once again.   I do like the sound on this one though. Tony you do a nice job on your rrecordings.  Show gets 5 stars because I feel its a real new years eve show with the 3rd set type of encores. If I had to put my New year shows in order it would be this 1 1st then 84 then 83 and 85 and 87 coming in last.
